rComments: She is the kind of prof you will see in high school- super bias and has favourites. Exceptionally rude for no reason and super intimidating. Absolutely hated being in her class as she has no respect for her students. Very condescending and has super vague questions with very specific answers. Avoid at all costs.

The prof is nice but the lectures are extremely basic for a 3rd year course. Discussions on ethical issues are topical, superficial and lack basic analysis. The course is a total catfish you will NOT be writing a research paper on a global health issue. The TAs and tutorials are great but the lectures are a complete and utter waste of time.

Dr. Dimaras is an amazing professor who is interested in what she teaches, which shows in her lectures and discussions of her work outside of class. She does assign a lot of articles, but most are easy to understand, and she reviews all of them in class. If you have the chance to take the ICM with her, DO IT! You won't regret it

Dr. Dimaras is really intelligent and passionate about her work, which is evident through taking her course. She has interesting lectures, which applicable content, and is super encouraging - her class atmosphere is very engaging and friendly! Be prepared to do work, but the work she assigns is interesting!
